enough troops to stop it.</sentence> <sentence ID="SENT-26" start="2470" end="2721">She admits, however, that, &quot;The <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Rwanda</ENAMEX>
<Event TYPE="Conflict" SUBTYPE="Attack">massacres</Event> occurred while <ENAMEX TYPE="PER">Annan</ENAMEX> was <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">U.N</ENAMEX>. Undersecretary General for
peacekeeping,&quot; and that &quot;After he became <ENAMEX TYPE="PER">SG</ENAMEX> [Secretary General], <ENAMEX TYPE="PER">Annan</ENAMEX>
commissioned a report to examine what had happened and suggest
remedies.&quot;</sentence> <sentence ID="SENT-27" start="2721" end="2805">Later, &quot;<ENAMEX TYPE="PER">Annan</ENAMEX> accepted responsibility for failing to act more
quickly,&quot; she writes.</sentence> <sentence ID="SENT-28" start="2805" end="2834">But responsibility for what?</sentence> <sentence ID="SENT-29" start="2834" end="3001">The truth is that, as
